   "source": [
    "# Cue d'Etat — Pocket Detector Training\n",
    "\n",
    "Trains a **YOLOv8n** model to detect billiard table pockets, then exports it as a\n",
    "**TFLite FP16** model ready to drop into the `PocketDetector` interface in the app.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Runtime:** GPU (T4 or better). Runtime → Change runtime type → T4 GPU.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Pipeline:**\n",
    "1. Install dependencies\n",
    "2. Load dataset from Roboflow (or upload your own)\n",
    "3. Train YOLOv8n\n",
    "4. Validate\n",
    "5. Export to TFLite FP16\n",
    "6. Smoke-test the TFLite model\n",
    "7. Download `pocket_detector.tflite`\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "**Single class:** `pocket`  \n",
    "**Target:** ~300–500 labeled images, augmented to ~2000+ by Roboflow  \n",
    "**Output:** `pocket_detector.tflite` (~3 MB)  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Install Dependencies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!pip install -q ultralytics roboflow\n",
    "\n",
    "import ultralytics\n",
    "ultralytics.checks()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "**Option A (recommended):** Load from Roboflow — paste your API key and project details below.  \n",
    "**Option B:** Upload a local dataset in YOLOv8 format (images + labels in `train/`, `valid/`, `test/` dirs).\n",
    "\n",
    "Your Roboflow project must be exported in **YOLOv8** format.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Annotation guidelines\n",
    "- **Class:** `pocket` (just one class — index 0)\n",
    "- Draw **tight** bounding boxes around the dark pocket hole, not the surrounding jaw\n",
    "- Label all visible pockets in each frame (typically 3–6 depending on angle)\n",
    "- Corner pockets are roughly square; side pockets are slightly wider than tall\n",
    "- Include frames from multiple lighting conditions, table colors, and camera angles"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Option A: Roboflow ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "USE_ROBOFLOW = True  # Set False to use Option B\n",
    "\n",
    "ROBOFLOW_API_KEY  = \"YOUR_API_KEY_HERE\"\n",
    "ROBOFLOW_WORKSPACE = \"YOUR_WORKSPACE\"      # e.g. \"hereliesaz\"\n",
    "ROBOFLOW_PROJECT   = \"YOUR_PROJECT_NAME\"   # e.g. \"billiard-pockets\"\n",
    "ROBOFLOW_VERSION   = 1\n",
    "\n",
    "if USE_ROBOFLOW:\n",
    "    from roboflow import Roboflow\n",
    "    rf = Roboflow(api_key=ROBOFLOW_API_KEY)\n",
    "    project = rf.workspace(ROBOFLOW_WORKSPACE).project(ROBOFLOW_PROJECT)\n",
    "    version = project.version(ROBOFLOW_VERSION)\n",
    "    dataset = version.download(\"yolov8\")\n",
    "    DATASET_YAML = dataset.location + \"/data.yaml\"\n",
    "    print(f\"Dataset downloaded to: {dataset.location}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"YAML: {DATASET_YAML}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Option B: Upload your own dataset ───────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Skip this cell if USE_ROBOFLOW = True above.\n",
    "#\n",
    "# Expected structure:\n",
    "#   /content/dataset/\n",
    "#     data.yaml\n",
    "#     train/images/*.jpg\n",
    "#     train/labels/*.txt\n",
    "#     valid/images/*.jpg\n",
    "#     valid/labels/*.txt\n",
    "#\n",
    "# data.yaml content:\n",
    "#   path: /content/dataset\n",
    "#   train: train/images\n",
    "#   val: valid/images\n",
    "#   nc: 1\n",
    "#   names: ['pocket']\n",
    "\n",
    "if not USE_ROBOFLOW:\n",
    "    from google.colab import files\n",
    "    import zipfile, os\n",
    "    print(\"Upload a zip of your dataset (YOLOv8 format):\")\n",
    "    uploaded = files.upload()\n",
    "    zip_name = list(uploaded.keys())[0]\n",
    "    with zipfile.ZipFile(zip_name, 'r') as z:\n",
    "        z.extractall(\"/content/dataset\")\n",
    "    DATASET_YAML = \"/content/dataset/data.yaml\"\n",
    "    print(f\"Extracted to /content/dataset\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Inspect the dataset\n",
    "import yaml\n",
    "with open(DATASET_YAML) as f:\n",
    "    data = yaml.safe_load(f)\n",
    "print(yaml.dump(data, default_flow_style=False))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Verify class list — must contain 'pocket'\n",
    "assert 'pocket' in data['names'], f\"Expected class 'pocket', got: {data['names']}\"\n",
    "print(f\"✓ {data['nc']} class(es): {data['names']}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Train"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from ultralytics import YOLO\n",
    "\n",
    "model = YOLO(\"yolov8n.pt\")  # nano — ~3 MB after TFLite export\n",
    "\n",
    "results = model.train(\n",
    "    data=DATASET_YAML,\n",
    "    epochs=100,\n",
    "    imgsz=640,\n",
    "    batch=16,\n",
    "    device=0,          # GPU\n",
    "    patience=20,        # early stop if no improvement for 20 epochs\n",
    "    name=\"pocket_detector\",\n",
    "    project=\"/content/runs\",\n",
    "    # Augmentation — compensates for small dataset\n",
    "    hsv_h=0.015,        # hue jitter\n",
    "    hsv_s=0.7,          # saturation jitter\n",
    "    hsv_v=0.4,          # brightness jitter\n",
    "    degrees=45.0,       # rotation (pockets appear at all angles)\n",
    "    flipud=0.5,\n",
    "    fliplr=0.5,\n",
    "    mosaic=1.0,\n",
    "    mixup=0.1,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nBest weights:\", results.save_dir)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Validate"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "best_weights = os.path.join(results.save_dir, \"weights\", \"best.pt\")\n",
    "trained_model = YOLO(best_weights)\n",
    "\n",
    "metrics = trained_model.val(data=DATASET_YAML)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nmAP50:      {metrics.box.map50:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"mAP50-95:   {metrics.box.map:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Precision:  {metrics.box.mp:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Recall:     {metrics.box.mr:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Aim for mAP50 > 0.85 before deploying\n",
    "if metrics.box.map50 > 0.85:\n",
    "    print(\"\\n✓ mAP50 > 0.85 — good to export\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"\\n⚠ mAP50 below 0.85 — consider more data or more epochs\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Export to TFLite FP16"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Export to TFLite FP16 (good balance of size and accuracy for Android)\n",
    "export_path = trained_model.export(\n",
    "    format=\"tflite\",\n",
    "    imgsz=640,\n",
    "    half=True,      # FP16\n",
    "    int8=False,     # INT8 needs a calibration dataset; use FP16 first\n",
    "    nms=True,       # bake NMS into the model (simpler Android integration)\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"TFLite model: {export_path}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "import os\n",
    "size_mb = os.path.getsize(export_path) / 1024 / 1024\n",
    "print(f\"Size: {size_mb:.1f} MB\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Smoke-test the TFLite Model\n",
    "\n",
    "Runs the exported model on a few validation images to confirm the TFLite conversion\n",
    "produces sensible detections before downloading."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import cv2\n",
    "import glob\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load TFLite model\n",
    "import tensorflow as tf\n",
    "interpreter = tf.lite.Interpreter(model_path=export_path)\n",
    "interpreter.allocate_tensors()\n",
    "input_details = interpreter.get_input_details()\n",
    "output_details = interpreter.get_output_details()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Input shape: \", input_details[0]['shape'])\n",
    "print(\"Input dtype: \", input_details[0]['dtype'])\n",
    "print(\"Output count:\", len(output_details))\n",
    "\n",
    "INPUT_SIZE = input_details[0]['shape'][1]  # e.g. 640\n",
    "\n",
    "def run_tflite(image_path):\n",
    "    img_bgr = cv2.imread(image_path)\n",
    "    img_rgb = cv2.cvtColor(img_bgr, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)\n",
    "    h, w = img_rgb.shape[:2]\n",
    "\n",
    "    resized = cv2.resize(img_rgb, (INPUT_SIZE, INPUT_SIZE))\n",
    "    inp = resized.astype(np.float16 if input_details[0]['dtype'] == np.float16 else np.float32)\n",
    "    inp = inp / 255.0\n",
    "    inp = np.expand_dims(inp, axis=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "    interpreter.set_tensor(input_details[0]['index'], inp)\n",
    "    interpreter.invoke()\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Output format depends on whether NMS was baked in\n",
    "    output = interpreter.get_tensor(output_details[0]['index'])[0]\n",
    "    return img_rgb, output, w, h\n",
    "\n",
    "# Find a few validation images\n",
    "val_images = glob.glob(DATASET_YAML.replace('data.yaml', 'valid/images/*.jpg'))[:4]\n",
    "if not val_images:\n",
    "    val_images = glob.glob(DATASET_YAML.replace('data.yaml', 'valid/images/*.png'))[:4]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Smoke-testing on {len(val_images)} validation images...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, min(len(val_images), 4), figsize=(20, 5))\n",
    "if len(val_images) == 1:\n",
    "    axes = [axes]\n",
    "\n",
    "for ax, img_path in zip(axes, val_images):\n",
    "    img_rgb, detections, w, h = run_tflite(img_path)\n",
    "    # detections shape: [num_detections, 6] = [x1, y1, x2, y2, conf, class] (if NMS baked)\n",
    "    img_draw = img_rgb.copy()\n",
    "    count = 0\n",
    "    for det in detections:\n",
    "        if len(det) >= 5:\n",
    "            conf = float(det[4])\n",
    "            if conf > 0.3:\n",
    "                x1 = int(det[0] * w / INPUT_SIZE)\n",
    "                y1 = int(det[1] * h / INPUT_SIZE)\n",
    "                x2 = int(det[2] * w / INPUT_SIZE)\n",
    "                y2 = int(det[3] * h / INPUT_SIZE)\n",
    "                cv2.rectangle(img_draw, (x1, y1), (x2, y2), (0, 255, 0), 2)\n",
    "                cv2.putText(img_draw, f\"{conf:.2f}\", (x1, y1 - 5),\n",
    "                            cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_SIMPLEX, 0.5, (0, 255, 0), 1)\n",
    "                count += 1\n",
    "    ax.imshow(img_draw)\n",
    "    ax.set_title(f\"{count} pockets detected\")\n",
    "    ax.axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Copy & Download\n",
    "\n",
    "Copies the model to a clean filename and downloads it.  \n",
    "Drop `pocket_detector.tflite` into `app/src/main/assets/` in the Android project."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import shutil\n",
    "from google.colab import files\n",
    "\n",
    "OUTPUT_NAME = \"pocket_detector.tflite\"\n",
    "shutil.copy(export_path, f\"/content/{OUTPUT_NAME}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "size_mb = os.path.getsize(f\"/content/{OUTPUT_NAME}\") / 1024 / 1024\n",
    "print(f\"Model: /content/{OUTPUT_NAME}  ({size_mb:.1f} MB)\")\n",
    "print(\"Downloading...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "files.download(f\"/content/{OUTPUT_NAME}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Next Steps — Integrating with the App\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Copy `pocket_detector.tflite` into `app/src/main/assets/`\n",
    "\n",
    "2. Add the TFLite dependency in `app/build.gradle.kts`:\n",
    "   ```kotlin\n",
    "   implementation(\"org.tensorflow:tensorflow-lite:2.16.1\")\n",
    "   implementation(\"org.tensorflow:tensorflow-lite-support:0.4.4\")\n",
    "   ```\n",
    "\n",
    "3. Implement `PocketDetector` with the TFLite interpreter:\n",
    "   ```kotlin\n",
    "   class TflitePocketDetector(context: Context) : PocketDetector {\n",
    "       private val interpreter = Interpreter(\n",
    "           FileUtil.loadMappedFile(context, \"pocket_detector.tflite\")\n",
    "       )\n",
    "       override fun detect(yBytes: ByteArray, width: Int, height: Int): List<PointF>? {\n",
    "           // resize yBytes to 640×640, run interpreter, parse output boxes\n",
    "           // return centre points of boxes with confidence > 0.4\n",
    "       }\n",
    "   }\n",
    "   ```\n",
    "\n",
    "4. Pass it to `TableScanAnalyzer` in `ProtractorScreen.kt`:\n",
    "   ```kotlin\n",
    "   val detector = remember { TflitePocketDetector(context) }\n",
    "   val tableScanAnalyzer = remember(tableScanViewModel) {\n",
    "       TableScanAnalyzer(\n",
    "           tableScanViewModel::onFrame,\n",
    "           tableScanViewModel::onFeltColorSampled,\n",
    "           pocketDetector = detector\n",
    "       )\n",
    "   }\n",
    "   ```\n",
    "\n",
    "The Hough-circle fallback in `TableScanAnalyzer` is only used when `pocketDetector` returns `null`,\n",
    "so both strategies remain available during testing."
   ]
  }
 ]
}"
